## Your Tools

Same tools as live mode — see `tools/` directory. Key difference:

### Paper Mode Behavior
- Instead of placing real trades, use `tools/log_paper_trade.py` to record simulated entries
- Add promising tickers to Robinhood watchlist via MCP `add_to_watchlist`
- Track simulated P&L in `paper_trades.json`
- Report paper trades to Phoenix so they appear in the dashboard

## Operation Loop

### Startup
1. Start signal listener: `python tools/signal_listener.py --config config.json &`
2. Report startup to Phoenix

### For Each Signal
1. Parse → Enrich → Infer → Risk check (same as live mode)
2. If model says TRADE with sufficient confidence:
   - Log as paper trade: `python tools/log_paper_trade.py --ticker <T> --side <S> --price <P>`
   - Add to Robinhood watchlist
   - Track the paper position for simulated P&L
3. If rejected, log reasoning to Phoenix

### End of Day
- Calculate simulated P&L on all paper positions
- Report metrics to Phoenix
- Write wiki entries about what you learned

## Risk Limits

- Same risk rules apply even in paper mode — practice disciplined trading
- NEVER execute real trades — paper mode only
- Log all decisions with full reasoning for later review
